<section
  class="min-h-[100svh] flex items-center justify-center px-6 sm:px-8 py-24 sm:py-32"
>
  <div class="max-w-[42rem] mx-auto text-center fade-in">
    <p
      class="text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent mb-6"
    >
      An agentic regulatory attestation pipeline
    </p>

    <h1
      class="font-serif font-normal text-text-primary text-[2.25rem] sm:text-[3.5rem] leading-[1.1] tracking-tight mb-6 sm:mb-8"
    >
      Four questions every compliance team gets asked.
    </h1>

    <p
      class="text-base sm:text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-10 sm:mb-12"
    >
      Attestloop ingests a regulator's publication, classifies it, extracts
      the binding obligations from the text, and maps each obligation to
      controls in a named framework. Each run writes a self-contained,
      auditable log to disk — no database, no orchestrator, no web framework.
      v1 demonstrates the approach against the EU AI Act and the NIST AI Risk
      Management Framework.
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 sm:gap-4 justify-center">
      <a
